         <entry xml:id="ambate-dlgenr"
                xml:lang="en"
                type="mainEntry"
                prev="#alsis-dlgenr"
                next="#androgynos-dlgenr"
                source="Genesis Rabbah">
            <form type="lemma" opt="false">
               <orth type="lemma" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false" select="true">אמבטי</orth>
               <orth type="transliteration" xml:lang="fjb" opt="false">ʾmbṭy</orth>
               <pron notation="rabbinic" opt="false">ambaṭe</pron>
               <gramGrp opt="false">
                  <gram type="pos" opt="false">noun</gram>
                  <gram type="gen" opt="false">f.</gram>
               </gramGrp>
               <form type="variant" source="K V" opt="false">
                  <orth xml:lang="jpa" opt="false">משל לאמטי</orth>
               </form>
               <form type="variant" source="Ox1" opt="false">
                  <orth xml:lang="jpa" opt="false">לאנבטי</orth>
               </form>
               <form type="variant" source="Vat1" opt="false">
                  <orth xml:lang="jpa" opt="false">לאומבטי</orth>
               </form>
            </form>
            <form type="inflected" opt="false">
               <orth xml:lang="jpa" opt="false" type="inflected">אמבטיות</orth>
               <orth type="transliteration" xml:lang="fjb" opt="false">ʾmbṭywt</orth>
               <pron notation="rabbinic" opt="false">ambaṭyot</pron>
               <gramGrp opt="false">
                  <gram type="gen" opt="false">pl.</gram>
               </gramGrp>
            </form>
            <sense xml:id="ambate-dlgenr-1" opt="false">
               <usg type="domain" opt="false">architecture</usg>
               <usg type="socioCultural" norm="borrowing" opt="false">cultural borrowing</usg>
               <usg type="normativity" opt="false">standard</usg>
               <usg type="meaningType" opt="false">lit.</usg>
               <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en" subtype="sense">
                  <quote>bath</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="translationEquivalent" xml:lang="grc">
                  <usg opt="false">
                     <lang opt="false">Post-Classical Greek</lang>
                  </usg>
                  <quote>ἐμβατή</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="example" xml:lang="jpa">
                  <quote>
            אמר ר' אליעזר לאמבטי שהיתה מלאה מים והיה בה ב' 
            <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">דיוסקוסים</ref> נאים, כל זמן שהיא מלאה מים לא היתה מלאכת דיוסקוסים} נראת, כיון שפתקה וניער המים מתוכה נראת מלאכת
            <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">דיוסקוסים</ref>
                  </quote>
                  <bibl default="false" status="draft">
                     <ref type="witness">10,2</ref>
                     <ref type="witness">I 75: 2-3</ref>
                  </bibl>
                  <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                     <quote>R. Eliʿezer said: [This may be compared] to a bath full of water, in which were two beautiful bas-reliefs; as long as it was full of water, the work of the bas-reliefs could not be seen; but when the plug was removed and the water emptied, the work of the bas-reliefs could be seen. (Freedman / Simon I 71)</quote>
                  </cit>
               </cit>
            </sense>
            <etym type="borrowing" opt="false">
               <lbl opt="false">source language</lbl>
               <lang opt="false">Post-Classical Greek+</lang>
               <cit type="etymon" xml:lang="grc">
                  <xr type="related" opt="false">
                     <lbl opt="false">Cf. LSJ</lbl>
                     <ref target="https://www.perseus.tufts.edu/hopper/text?doc=Perseus%3Atext%3A1999.04.0057%3Aalphabetic+letter%3D*e%3Aentry+group%3D83%3Aentry%3De%29mbato%2Fs"
                          type="entry">ἐμβατή, II.</ref>
                  </xr>
               </cit>
            </etym>
            <note anchored="true">
            = 
      <bibl type="ancient" default="false" status="draft">Yalq 16 [5b: 55]</bibl>;
      <bibl type="ancient" default="false" status="draft">YalqProv 961 [498d: 59]</bibl>;
      <bibl type="ancient" default="false" status="draft">YalqM Prov 25,4 [55a]</bibl>
            </note>
            <note xml:lang="jpa" anchored="true">ישובו רשעים לשאולה, ר' אבא בר זבדא אמר לאמבטי התחתונה שבגיהנם.
      <bibl default="false" status="draft">
                  <ref type="witness">86,2</ref>
                  <ref type="witness">II 1053: 5</ref>
               </bibl>
            </note>
            <note xml:lang="en" anchored="true">
               = 
      <bibl type="ancient" default="false" status="draft">GenR 50,3 [II 518: 5]</bibl> (
      <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">ביטי</ref>);
      <bibl type="ancient" default="false" status="draft">GenR 68,8 [II 777: 2]</bibl> (
      <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">בוטי</ref>)
   </note>
            <note xml:lang="en" anchored="true">
               The wicked shall return ‘li-sheʾolah’ – to the netherworld (Ps 9,18). Said R. Abbaʾ b. Zavdah: That means to the nethermost [bath] of hell. (cf. Freedman / Simon I 435)
   </note>
            <note xml:lang="en" anchored="true">
               Pl. not in GenR. Common in Rabbinic literature. The reading of GenR 86,2 is certainly corrupted. Cf. 
      <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Heijmanns (2013) 36</bibl>.
   </note>
            <ref type="bibliography">
               <bibl default="false" status="draft">
                  <title>Sokoloff, DJPA</title>
                  <citedRange>37a</citedRange>
               </bibl>
            </ref>
         </entry>
